The paper discusses a technique for improving data veracity in big data, which is a topic that falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The technique involves using sparse linear algebra, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of databases such as SciDB and Apache Accumulo, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
